    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-06T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="421"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.00/2109: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Armour</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-06T14:00:00-03:00"
                            >November 6, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2630. Embassy’s telegram No. 2610, November 3, 8 p.m.<note n="59"
                        xml:id="d421fn59">Not printed.</note> Various delegations of army officers
                    estimated by <hi rend="italic">El Pueblo</hi> to number about 300 persons,
                    visited the Foreign Minister yesterday afternoon to express their complete
                    support of his recent declarations to correspondent of Santiago newspaper <hi
                        rend="italic">El Mercurio</hi> that the policy of Argentina is one of
                    complete and absolute neutrality.</p>
                <p>Foregoing item is carried in all papers and was evidently officially
                    inspired.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Embassy at Santiago.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Armour</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
